What is the difference between *git merge* and *git rebase*?

merge  = joins two branches together (creates extra commit)
rebase = moves your commits on top of another branch (clean history)

"On Top" Means

BEFORE rebase:
B is base of D and E
D and E sit on top of B

A в†’ B в†’ D в†’ E
         в†‘
      base of D

AFTER rebase:
C becomes new base of D and E
D and E sit on top of C

A в†’ B в†’ C в†’ D в†’ E
              в†‘
         new base of D вњ…
-------------------------------
Simple One Liner
-----------------------------
"on top" = your commits D and E
           now start from C
           instead of B вњ…

Base of D changed from B to C вЂ” that's why it's called re-base! рџ™‚
-------------------------------------------------------
Simple Rule

rebase rewrites history  в†’ never do on main вќЊ
merge keeps history      в†’ safe on main вњ…

Same code, new identity вЂ” that's what rebase does! рџ™‚
-----------------------------------------------------
What Gets Rewritten

BEFORE rebase:
D = commit hash abc123  (based on B)
E = commit hash def456  (based on D)

AFTER rebase:
D'= commit hash xyz789  (based on C) в†ђ new hash!
E'= commit hash pqr012  (based on D')в†ђ new hash!

Same code вЂ” but different commit hash вњ…
-----------------------
Why Hash Changes

Git commit hash is based on:
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ code changes
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ author
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ timestamp
в””в”Ђв”Ђ PARENT COMMIT  в†ђ this changes!

D was based on B в†’ hash = abc123
D now based on C в†’ hash = xyz789  в†ђ parent changed so hash changes

Merge Doesn't Rewrite

MERGE:
D = abc123  в†ђ same hash, never changes вњ…
E = def456  в†ђ same hash, never changes вњ…
M = new merge commit created

REBASE:
D'= xyz789  в†ђ new hash вљ пёЏ
E'= pqr012  в†ђ new hash вљ пёЏ
no merge commit
-------------------------------------
Why Rewriting is Dangerous on Main

You have D  = abc123
Teammate has D = abc123  в†ђ same

You rebase main
Now D'= xyz789  в†ђ different!

Teammate still has abc123
You now have xyz789
в†’ Git thinks they are different commits вќЊ
в†’ causes conflicts for everyone вљ пёЏ
